      <data key="d7">FUNGI IN THE INDOOR AIR OF CRITICAL HOSPITAL AREAS: A REVIEW</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE FUNGI IN CRITICAL HOSPITAL AREAS</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">The review targets airborne fungi as the primary microbial contaminants of concern in critical hospital areas.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT AND COVID-19: A REVIEW FOR SURGEONS" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT AND COVID-19: A REVIEW FOR SURGEONS</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">The PPE strategies discussed in the review are aimed at preventing transmission of COVID-19 (SARS-CoV-2) to and from surgeons in clinical settings.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.85</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b_chunk_5</data>
      <data key="d14">3fc1e87d-c54a-447e-9229-2850cf6a1b9b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION FAN OPERATION" target="ACH IN THE BUS">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION FAN OPERATION</data>
      <data key="d8">ACH IN THE BUS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Operating the bus ventilation fans (front and/or rear) alters the ACH in the bus, increasing the rate of air exchange compared with no fan operation.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION FAN OPERATION" target="INHALATION VOLUME OF CO2 RELATIVE TO THE VOLUME EMITTED">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION FAN OPERATION</data>
      <data key="d8">INHALATION VOLUME OF CO2 RELATIVE TO THE VOLUME EMITTED</data>
      <data key="d9">REDUCES</data>
      <data key="d10">Operating the bus ventilation fans lowers the relative inhalation volume of CO2 by enhancing air mixing and exchange, thereby decreasing local CO2 (and surrogate pathogen) concentrations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="VENTILATION FAN OPERATION" target="BUS CABIN">
      <data key="d7">VENTILATION FAN OPERATION</data>
      <data key="d8">BUS CABIN</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">Operation of the front and rear ventilation fans is applied to the bus cabin to improve air circulation and ventilation for occupants.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="FRONT VENTILATION FAN" target="ACH IN THE BUS">
      <data key="d7">FRONT VENTILATION FAN</data>
      <data key="d8">ACH IN THE BUS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Use of the front ventilation fan contributes to the overall ACH in the bus, particularly affecting airflow and air exchange in the front region.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="REAR VENTILATION FAN" target="ACH IN THE BUS">
      <data key="d7">REAR VENTILATION FAN</data>
      <data key="d8">ACH IN THE BUS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Use of the rear ventilation fan contributes to the overall ACH in the bus, particularly influencing air exchange in the rear region.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="OPEN WINDOWS" target="ACH IN THE BUS">
      <data key="d7">OPEN WINDOWS</data>
      <data key="d8">ACH IN THE BUS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Opening bus windows changes and generally increases the air changes per hour (ACH) in the bus cabin, with different numbers and configurations of open windows producing different ACH values.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_4</data>
