      <data key="d7">MULTI-SCALE RISK ASSESSMENT AND MITIGATIONS COMPARISON FOR COVID-19 IN URBAN PUBLIC TRANSPORT</data>
      <data key="d8">MITIGATIONS FOR COVID-19 IN URBAN PUBLIC TRANSPORT</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The multi-scale risk assessment study evaluates and compares the effectiveness of different mitigation strategies for COVID-19 in urban public transport, providing evidence for their performance.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="MULTI-SCALE RISK ASSESSMENT AND MITIGATIONS COMPARISON FOR COVID-19 IN URBAN PUBLIC TRANSPORT" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">MULTI-SCALE RISK ASSESSMENT AND MITIGATIONS COMPARISON FOR COVID-19 IN URBAN PUBLIC TRANSPORT</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">REDUCES</data>
      <data key="d10">By quantifying risk and comparing mitigations, the study characterizes how certain strategies can reduce COVID-19 transmission risk in public transport settings.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="SPATIAL DISTRIBUTIONS OF AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION RISK ON COMMUTER BUSES" target="AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION RISK ON COMMUTER BUSES">
      <data key="d7">SPATIAL DISTRIBUTIONS OF AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION RISK ON COMMUTER BUSES</data>
      <data key="d8">AIRBORNE TRANSMISSION RISK ON COMMUTER BUSES</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The numerical case study generates and analyzes spatial distributions of airborne transmission risk on commuter buses using computational fluid and particle dynamics.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.9</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PERFORMANCE OF CO2 ACCUMULATION AND DROPLET DISPERSION FROM A COUGH INSIDE A HOSPITAL LIFT UNDER DIFFERENT VENTILATION STRATEGIES" target="VENTILATION STRATEGIES">
      <data key="d7">PERFORMANCE OF CO2 ACCUMULATION AND DROPLET DISPERSION FROM A COUGH INSIDE A HOSPITAL LIFT UNDER DIFFERENT VENTILATION STRATEGIES</data>
      <data key="d8">VENTILATION STRATEGIES</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The study provides quantitative evidence on how various ventilation strategies influence CO2 accumulation and droplet dispersion, effectively characterizing their performance in a hospital lift context.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="PERFORMANCE OF CO2 ACCUMULATION AND DROPLET DISPERSION FROM A COUGH INSIDE A HOSPITAL LIFT UNDER DIFFERENT VENTILATION STRATEGIES" target="HOSPITAL LIFT">
      <data key="d7">PERFORMANCE OF CO2 ACCUMULATION AND DROPLET DISPERSION FROM A COUGH INSIDE A HOSPITAL LIFT UNDER DIFFERENT VENTILATION STRATEGIES</data>
      <data key="d8">HOSPITAL LIFT</data>
      <data key="d9">APPLIED_TO</data>
      <data key="d10">The study is specifically conducted in a hospital lift, making the elevator environment the context in which ventilation strategies are assessed.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.8</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_7</data>
