    <edge source="WIND VELOCITY AND DISPERSION/ADVECTION-DIFFUSION OF ARTIFICIAL DROPLETS AND DROPLET NUCLEI IN A DOMED ALL-WEATHER MULTI-PURPOSE STADIUM" target="WIND VELOCITY">
      <data key="d7">WIND VELOCITY AND DISPERSION/ADVECTION-DIFFUSION OF ARTIFICIAL DROPLETS AND DROPLET NUCLEI IN A DOMED ALL-WEATHER MULTI-PURPOSE STADIUM</data>
      <data key="d8">WIND VELOCITY</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">The study varies or characterizes wind velocity as a key environmental rate parameter influencing droplet and droplet nuclei dispersion in the stadium.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="WIND VELOCITY AND DISPERSION/ADVECTION-DIFFUSION OF ARTIFICIAL DROPLETS AND DROPLET NUCLEI IN A DOMED ALL-WEATHER MULTI-PURPOSE STADIUM" target="DISPERSION/ADVECTION-DIFFUSION OF ARTIFICIAL DROPLETS AND DROPLET NUCLEI">
      <data key="d7">WIND VELOCITY AND DISPERSION/ADVECTION-DIFFUSION OF ARTIFICIAL DROPLETS AND DROPLET NUCLEI IN A DOMED ALL-WEATHER MULTI-PURPOSE STADIUM</data>
      <data key="d8">DISPERSION/ADVECTION-DIFFUSION OF ARTIFICIAL DROPLETS AND DROPLET NUCLEI</data>
      <data key="d9">VALIDATED_BY</data>
      <data key="d10">The study quantifies how different wind velocity conditions affect the dispersion and advection-diffusion of artificial droplets and droplet nuclei, providing modeled outcomes for these spread patterns.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_7</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CDC SCIENTIFIC BRIEF: SARS-COV-2 TRANSMISSION (UPDATED MAY 7, 2021)" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">CDC SCIENTIFIC BRIEF: SARS-COV-2 TRANSMISSION (UPDATED MAY 7, 2021)</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">The CDC scientific brief specifically focuses on the transmission characteristics of SARS-CoV-2 as its primary pathogen of interest.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.95</data>
      <data key="d12">1</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CDC SCIENTIFIC BRIEF: SARS-COV-2 TRANSMISSION (UPDATED MAY 7, 2021)" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">CDC SCIENTIFIC BRIEF: SARS-COV-2 TRANSMISSION (UPDATED MAY 7, 2021)</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">By examining how SARS-CoV-2 spreads, the CDC scientific brief implicitly targets COVID-19 as the associated disease outcome under discussion.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AEROSOLS (MESH)" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">AEROSOLS (MESH)</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">Research indexed under the MeSH term 'Aerosols' includes studies of airborne particles that can transport SARS-CoV-2, thereby addressing this pathogen in the context of aerosol transmission.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="AIR POLLUTION, INDOOR / ANALYSIS (MESH MAJOR TOPIC)" target="SARS-COV-2">
      <data key="d7">AIR POLLUTION, INDOOR / ANALYSIS (MESH MAJOR TOPIC)</data>
      <data key="d8">SARS-COV-2</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">Analytical studies of indoor air pollution often investigate indoor airborne contaminants, including the potential presence and behavior of SARS-CoV-2 in indoor air.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.6</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="CARBON DIOXIDE (MESH)" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">CARBON DIOXIDE (MESH)</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">Literature under the 'Carbon Dioxide' MeSH heading in this context frequently examines CO₂ as an indicator of ventilation and occupancy in studies related to COVID-19 transmission risk.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.55</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HUMANS (MESH)" target="COVID-19">
      <data key="d7">HUMANS (MESH)</data>
      <data key="d8">COVID-19</data>
      <data key="d9">TARGETS</data>
      <data key="d10">The 'Humans' MeSH term indicates that the COVID-19 and indoor air quality research referenced is conducted in or directly relevant to human populations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.5</data>
      <data key="d12">3</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_9</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HUMANS" target="CARBON DIOXIDE">
      <data key="d7">HUMANS</data>
      <data key="d8">CARBON DIOXIDE</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Humans generate carbon dioxide at a characteristic rate through respiration, and the aggregate CO₂ emission from occupants determines the indoor CO₂ load that must be removed by ventilation to maintain acceptable concentrations.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.75</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="HUMANS" target="AEROSOLS">
      <data key="d7">HUMANS</data>
      <data key="d8">AEROSOLS</data>
      <data key="d9">HAS_DOSE</data>
      <data key="d10">Humans emit respiratory aerosols at a rate that depends on activities such as breathing, speaking, and coughing, establishing the source term for airborne particles that ventilation and other controls must dilute or remove.</data>
      <data key="d11">0.7</data>
      <data key="d12">2</data>
      <data key="d13">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_10</data>
      <data key="d14">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </edge>
